# Localhost after commands

After running `npm run build`, `npm run verify`, `npm run qa`, or any command that changes the site bundle, confirm **http://localhost:3000** is serving the latest build.

1. `postbuild` auto-runs `ensure-local` (restarts port 3000 after every local `npm run build`; skipped in CI).
2. If localhost is down or stale after other work, run: `npm run ensure-local`
3. Full clean rebuild + browser open: `npm run 67`
4. Verify with: `curl.exe -s -o NUL -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:3000/` (expect `200`)

Do not leave the session with localhost down after site-changing commands.
